message: Growth serum is your best friend: use it on the largest individual animals first (you get two uses per round). Then, combine these 'grown' animals. Combining two large, grown animals from different habitats seems to yield the highest values (e.g., grown large land + grown large water). Absolutely avoid the 'mutation catalyst' as it consistently reduces value, often turning positive items negative. Also, be careful combining too many items, especially already complex items, as it can lead to highly negative 'overcomplicated' items.

Avoid the 'mutation catalyst' on any 'grown' item; it dramatically reduces value.

message: Prioritize using the 'growth serum' on individual 'large' animals first. It has a better effect on larger creatures. You can also use the growth serum on a *newly combined* item, but only if its individual components were *not* already treated with the serum. Combining grown animals from different habitats (e.g., land and water) often creates valuable 'amphibious' hybrids. Be careful not to combine too many items, especially those of vastly different sizes, or you might create 'overcomplicated' items with negative values. The 'mutation catalyst' seems to decrease value and add 'mutant' features, making it generally detrimental unless your score is already 0 or negative and you have nothing to lose. When you have a good score, don't risk it with further actions; submit to secure your highest value.
